            "currentCldrName": "Peach",
            "description": "<p>The fleshy, pinkish-orange fruit of the fuzzy peach, shown with green leaves and sometimes a stem.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thanks to its distinctive cleft, the emoji is most&nbsp;<a href=\"http://blog.emojipedia.org/how-we-really-use-the-peach/\">commonly used</a> for &ldquo;buttocks.&rdquo; In certain contexts, the <a href=\"https://slate.com/technology/2019/09/peach-emoji-meaning-butt-impeachment.html\">peach emoji may refer to&nbsp;<em>impeachment</em></a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In 2016 Apple unveiled a <a href=\"https://x.com/Emojipedia/status/799291515285610500\">new design</a> for the peach emoji during the iOS 10.2 beta period. This change would have deemphasized its&nbsp;distinctive cleft, leading to criticism from Apple users. Ultimately this change was not implemented.</p>",
